The initiator and CEO of Mark D Ball Basketball Championships, Mr. Igoche Mark, has lauded the contributions of various stakeholders and individuals towards the huge success of the 10th edition of the championship held in Abuja, the nation’s capital. Mark, in a thank you message, his personally signed on behalf the organisers of the 2022 Mark D Ball Basketball Championship, said the success of this year’s championships which saw a total of twenty four(24) elite men’s teams and sixteen(16) women’s teams compete for honours, testifies to the irreversible fact that the new era of the nation’s domestic basketball, as enunciated by his pet project, “The New Face of Nigeria’s Basketball’ is well underway and fully on course to achieving greatness. Mark is also the president of the Nigeria Basketball Federation (NBBF) faction showered praises on the Ministry of Youth and Sports Development, NBBF officials referees, technical officials, club owners, security operatives, coaches, players and media personnel for their unflinching and professional support throughout the championships. Mark ended the statement by pledging his loyalty to all facets of the slam and dunk game in Nigeria; restating his commitment toward investing resources and time to engender a rancour free NBBF, promoting unity amongst all stakeholders, sponsors and lovers of the game. 